        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Styling a Solitaire Ring for Brunch or Casual Weekend Outings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Styling a Solitaire Ring for Brunch or Casual Weekend Outings</h2><p>Weekend brunches and casual outings give you more freedom to play with your jewellery. This is where solitaire rings can be styled in a more relaxed and creative way.</p><p>Stacking rings is a popular choice for casual looks. A design like the Elegant Solitaire Stackable Ring works well with slim gold bands or textured rings.</p>",
            "custom_id": "styling-a-solitaire",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_9KhX3Y": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Styling_a_Solitaire_Ring_for_Brunch_or_Casual_Weekend_Outings.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qwTzXx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Some easy ways to style it include:</p><p>1.] Wearing the solitaire with two thin stacking bands<br/>2.] Pairing it with small hoop earrings or diamond studs<br/>3.] Matching it with relaxed outfits like summer dresses, linen shirts, or denim<br/><br/>Another great option is the Portuguese Solitaire Bypass Ring, which has a flowing band design that feels modern and slightly playful. It works beautifully with casual outfits while still looking refined.</p><p>For brunch styling, the goal is effortless elegance rather than a heavily layered look.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_F4mH3W": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
